Question 1

a)

get_angle <- function(x, y) {
  angle <- acos(t(x)%*%y/(norm(x,type="2")*norm(y,type="2")))
  angle <- angle * (180/pi)
  
  #here, we use the determinant to deduce the direction
  #negative determinant represents a clockwise orientation so we do (360-angle)
  if (x[1]*y[2] - x[2]*y[1] < 0) {
    angle <- 360 - angle
  }
  angle
}

b)

get_angle(c(2,0), c(cos(27*pi/180),sin(27*pi/180))) # will return 27

get_angle(c(-1,1), c(-1,-1)) # will return 90
##      [,1]
## [1,]   90
get_angle(c(0,1), c(1,0)) # will return 270
##      [,1]
## [1,]  270
